==English==
===Etymology===
Derived from Neo-Latin ''[[puerperalis]]'', from Latin ''[[puerpera]]'' meaning "woman in childbirth", from Latin ''[[puer]]'' meaning "child, boy, male slave" + ''[[parere]]'' "to bear children"

===Adjective===
'''puerperal'''

#Of or pertaining to or associated with [[childbirth]].
